<subSubSection id="C316C8D5FFBFFFE4FF657B5B435056B3" pageId="1" pageNumber="212" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB39B5EFFBFFFE4FF657B5B435056B3" blockId="1.[174,1233,1339,1846]" pageId="1" pageNumber="212">
D i a g n o s i s. Slender and smaller species: wing length 5–8 (–9) mm; scutellum with one pair of sctl setae, if with 2 pairs, then fore trochanter of female without spiny setulae, ventral hooks of oviscape sharp and slender; male genitalia (known only for 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CE0DDFFBFFFE4FBB37B1C439D5690" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[1077,1232,1403,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Apyrgota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinifemur">
<emphasis id="B978474CFFBFFFE4FBB37B1C439D5690" box="[1077,1232,1403,1429]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="212">E. spinifemur</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CE0DDFFBFFFE4FF677BFC46CD56B0" authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[225,384,1436,1461]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictiventris">
<emphasis id="B978474CFFBFFFE4FF677BFC46CD56B0" box="[225,384,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="212">E. pictiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
): surstylus short, epandrium subquadrate in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C316C8D5FFBFFFE4FF657BDB44785433" pageId="1" pageNumber="212" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB39B5EFFBFFFE4FF657BDB44785433" blockId="1.[174,1233,1339,1846]" pageId="1" pageNumber="212">
